{"expireTime":9007200844372252000,"key":"transformer-remark-markdown-html-38d74355c2d8123d82cdc7f1b3abcf71-gatsby-remark-imagesgatsby-remark-responsive-iframegatsby-remark-prismjsgatsby-remark-copy-linked-filesgatsby-remark-smartypants-","val":"<p>Learning to pull data from APIs is a powerful, powerful thing. Let’s face it: we are data addicted. We love posting information, consuming information, learning new things from information. You get the point. We are surrounded by APIs filled with data ready to use.</p>\n<p>Let’s create a small react app to show how to fetch API data. As a note: this assumes you understand REST API concepts and understand react</p>\n<!-- ![unstopabble gif](./unstoppable.gif) -->\n<p>Let’s get started!</p>\n<h2>First steps</h2>\n<p>This first thing we want to do is create a new react app. Open up your terminal and enter <code class=\"language-text\">npx create-react-app &lt;your-app-name&gt;</code></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/82f5b120fa9ae8233e37f79be8495175/e628c/cra.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 6.081081081081082%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABQAAAABCAYAAADeko4lAAAACXBIWXMAAAsSAAALEgHS3X78AAAAQklEQVQI1yXGWw6AMAgFUQoFLaUPjfvf6pXox2QO2WC0i3Fuhj/pm3HM/xYFYgXqDO2SDlQfqH1CY6dnekFagIi+Xla8FaraHAZqAAAAAElFTkSuQmCC'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"create-react-app\"\n        title=\"create-react-app\"\n        src=\"/static/82f5b120fa9ae8233e37f79be8495175/fcda8/cra.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/82f5b120fa9ae8233e37f79be8495175/12f09/cra.png 148w,\n/static/82f5b120fa9ae8233e37f79be8495175/e4a3f/cra.png 295w,\n/static/82f5b120fa9ae8233e37f79be8495175/fcda8/cra.png 590w,\n/static/82f5b120fa9ae8233e37f79be8495175/e628c/cra.png 619w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Once it has finished installing the files, go ahead and change into the app directory you just made <code class=\"language-text\">cd &lt;your-app-name&gt;</code> and then type <code class=\"language-text\">yarn start</code></p>\n<p>Doing this will begin a dev server. Initially, because we used create-react-app, the page will be filled with a React logo and a link to the docs like so:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/e992be04acc628ecdc4145de8ef36bf2/07a9c/lhost.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62.83783783783784%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"lhost\"\n        title=\"lhost\"\n        src=\"/static/e992be04acc628ecdc4145de8ef36bf2/fcda8/lhost.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/e992be04acc628ecdc4145de8ef36bf2/12f09/lhost.png 148w,\n/static/e992be04acc628ecdc4145de8ef36bf2/e4a3f/lhost.png 295w,\n/static/e992be04acc628ecdc4145de8ef36bf2/fcda8/lhost.png 590w,\n/static/e992be04acc628ecdc4145de8ef36bf2/efc66/lhost.png 885w,\n/static/e992be04acc628ecdc4145de8ef36bf2/c83ae/lhost.png 1180w,\n/static/e992be04acc628ecdc4145de8ef36bf2/07a9c/lhost.png 1440w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Go ahead and open up the app in your editor of choice. Personally I use vscode, but it doesn’t really matter. Once open, let’s delete some of the template stuff included in create-react-app. Delete the test files, logo.svg, the serviceworker file, and go ahead and structure the project.</p>\n<p>I like to have a src/styles folder for all my scss, a src/container for my app.jsx file, and a src/components folder, while leaving src/index.jsx where it’s at.</p>\n<p><img src=\"\"></p>"}